TableContextTimeStampAfterTable: {24800=2013, 25329=2012 In her first season at UCSB, Madison Beckley came off the bench and played 16 matches...Tallied two goals on the year, one apiece against Weber State and UC Davis...Also had one assist for a total of five points...Had 13 shots, seven on-goal...Her seven shots on-goal ranked fifth on the team. HIGH SCHOOL/CLUB Beckley attended Aliso Niguel High School...Coached by Randy Dodge...Named First Team All-South Coast Conference...At the club level, played for Slammers FC of Newport Beach, Calif....Also ran track at Aliso Niguel where she set a school record in the 300 meter low hurdles. OHIO STATE Beckley played her freshman season at Ohio State...Saw action in five matches for the Buckeyes, including a loss in the NCAA Tournament to Duke. PERSONAL Madison Beckley was born Oct. 19, 1993 in Newport Beach, Calif....The daughter of Joele Watson and Scott Beckley...Hopes to major in communication studies and would like to become a sports reporter or a sideline reporter.}
